  "created": "2025-10-08",
  "description": "The stringent response is a global regulatory mechanism activated by amino acid starvation and other nutrient limitations. The alarmone (p)ppGpp, synthesized by RelA in response to uncharged tRNA accumulation, dramatically reprograms cellular metabolism by inhibiting rRNA/tRNA transcription and growth-related processes while activating amino acid biosynthesis and stress responses. This system coordinates ~500 genes to shift from rapid growth to survival mode.",
  "id": "ecoli_stringent_response",
